modules.description: This module handles serialization and deserialization of BIL (Binary Intermediate Language) components using various formats such as JSON, Protocol Buffers, and Piqi. It provides functions to convert between string representations and BIL structures like `bil`, `stmt`, and `exp`, as well as mappings between Piqi expressions and BIL variables. Concrete use cases include parsing BIL code from external sources and exporting BIL data for storage or transmission in a structured format.

This module implements serialization and deserialization of BAP intermediate representation (IR) terms to and from multiple formats including JSON, Protocol Buffers, Piqi, and XML. It supports direct conversion of strings to typed IR terms like programs, subroutines, blocks, arguments, phi nodes, and definitions, and vice versa. Use cases include loading BAP IR from external sources, exporting analysis results, and interoperation with tools that consume structured data formats.
